# General Project Guidelines

## Documentation
- Read `.cursor/project-context.md` for a complete overview of the project
- Consult README.md for installation and development instructions
- Review CONTRIBUTING.md before making contributions
- Check the file structure in project-context.md

## Project Structure
- src/ - Source code
- public/ - Static assets and extension manifest
- scripts/ - Build and utility scripts
- dist/ - Build output (generated)

## Development Workflow
- Use `npm run dev` for general development
- Use `npm run dev:extension` for extension development
- Build with `npm run build` or `npm run build:extension`

## Code Quality
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Maintain code consistency with existing patterns
- Keep components modular and focused
- Handle errors gracefully

## Feature Development
- Maintain backward compatibility when adding features
- Ensure new features don't interfere with existing functionality
- Test on multiple platforms and browsers

## Code Style
- Use consistent formatting throughout the codebase
- Follow naming conventions established in the project
- Keep code clean and readable
- Document complex logic with comments

## Work With Existing Tools
- Leverage React's component-based architecture
- Use the DrawingContext for state management
- Utilize custom hooks for reusable logic
- Follow Tailwind CSS for styling
